500|$|Sir William Heygate Edmund Colborne [...] "Billy" [...] Butlin (29 September 1899 – 12 June 1980) was a British, South Africa-born {{entrepreneur}} {{whose name}} is synonymous with the British <b>holiday</b> <b>camp.</b> Although <b>holiday</b> <b>camps</b> such as Warner's existed {{in one form or}} another before Butlin opened his first in 1936, it was Butlin who turned <b>holiday</b> <b>camps</b> into a multimillion-pound industry and an important aspect of British culture.|$|R
